      "text": "Last Alert (known as Red Alert in Europe and Japan) is a single-player top down shooting game developed by Sin-Nihon Laser Soft. It was released in Japan in 1989 and North America in 1990 for the TurboGrafx-CD. The story is that of a lone soldier whose unit has been wiped out who has been tasked by the CIA to take down an international criminal syndicate.",
